				<outline text="The border continues to be a problem because those in power want it to be a problem. The purpose is redirection, don't pay attention to &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theatlantic.com/magazine/archive/2024/03/facebook-meta-silicon-valley-politics/677168/&quot;&gt;what the oligarchs are doing&lt;/a&gt;, keep your attention on what I tell you the problem is while I take more away from you to give to myself. It's all a distraction. Trump is a distraction. Biden is a distraction.  Israel, Palestine, Gaza...all real problems not be be solved so that they are a distraction." created="Tue, 30 Jan 2024 15:09:36 GMT" type="outline"/>
				<outline text="I think the biggest argument that should be made to the American people is that you are being used. I get the feeling that everything is so bad that it might as well all be blown up, but every crater created by an explosion is eventually filled, so you better &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theatlantic.com/magazine/archive/2024/03/facebook-meta-silicon-valley-politics/677168/&quot;&gt;beware of what will come after&lt;/a&gt; everything is blown up as there no guarantees it will be better for you!  Take &lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Red_pill_and_blue_pill&quot;&gt;the red pill&lt;/a&gt;. It's not good enough to just want change, to just oppose whatever is, we need to be able to know and communicate what is to go into the crater after the explosion." created="Tue, 30 Jan 2024 15:19:10 GMT" type="outline"/>
